metadata.name: Blendokush #146
metadata.description:
Inspired by the Android game, "Blendoku", this is an exploration into combining graduated colour arrays in different ways. Each piece begins with a set of 9 base colours. 
Keyboard 'c' will randomly change the way that the colours are combined while keeping all other variations the same.

metadata.name: Allégories booléennes #264
metadata.description:
"Allégories booléennes" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at PARIS+ par Art Basel

This work is a continuation of research around the intersections of shapes that I have been exploring for a while. I wonder about the way in which they make it possible to bring out new compositions from superpositions of shapes that could initially represent a real disorder.

Controls:
• "a": Play the animation
• "s": Export the image (default 2160 × 3840px PNG)
• "h": Change export settings to high resolution (then press "s" to export a 6480 ×11520px PNG)
• "m": Change export settings to medium resolution (then press "s" to export a 4320 × 7680px PNG)
• "n": Back to 2160 × 3840px

Artwork by Julien Espagnon, 2022.

metadata.name: Different Intersections - Iteration 4 #155
metadata.description:
This is the culmination of a series of iterations

____ - Iteration 1
____ - Iteration 2
____ - Iteration 3

The iterations were released under the pseudonym Extracurricular Activities.

The algorithmic theme of the iterations was extensive usage of boolean operations (intersection and difference) on polygons to derive interesting composite shapes.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: Algorithm, be my guide #230
metadata.description:
At length, I summoned the courage to approach.

-

I was worn. Months of aimless wandering have culminated in this series; a meditation on my struggles to find a direction in my life and with my art.

At times paralyzed by too many possibilities, and at other times completely void of ideas. I was lost in the depths of my thinking, overwhelmed by indecision and doubt.

Generative works are a form of process art, yet along the way I’d forgotten to “trust the process”. It was time to cede control and let each line of code light the way.

-

This project paints on a 2D canvas, pixel by pixel. I used a custom projection that blends isometric and perspective techniques, to create an uncanny viewpoint between the two. Objects are randomly generated, then an algorithm applies color mixing and position displacement to each pixel as it’s rendered.

By default the canvas has 2k pixels on its longest edge. You can change this in live view by pressing any number from 1-9. For example, pressing ‘4’ would render it with 4k pixels along the longest edge. I recommend ‘4’, but this can take up to a few minutes to render.

Press ‘s’ to save the rendered image.

metadata.name: UPLOAD.EXE #207
metadata.description:
No death in the metaverse 
100 billion mortal coils before us, reduced to silly memes 

Here then, a chance to right every wrong 
Or curse ourselves, forgetting we once counted days so keenly 

C:\SOULS>UPLOAD.EXE -commit -purge 
Irreversible operation. Are you sure? [Y/N] Y_ 

.....LFG 

---------------------------------------------------- 


Additional params 

&fullsize=true : 4096x4096 output 
&debug=true : Display generative figure outlines  
&notilt=true : Remove tilt-shift filter 


References 

How to draw a basic Human Figure Using Circles Only - Photoshop - Easy Anatomy Drawing Tutorial  
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TgIYpe4dPWo 


Libraries (refer licenses.js) 

pixijs/pixijs - Graphics 
bjornharrtell/jsts – Polygon routines 
meodai/poline - Colour routines 
jwagner/simplex-noise - Noise gen 
strainer/fdrandom - Random number gen

metadata.name: re:build #93
metadata.description:
A daydream on sheets of vellum.

Press '1', '2', or '3' in live view to increase resolution
Press 't' to toggle paper texture (to print without texture)
Press 's' to save a .png

metadata.name: Cylinders #214
metadata.description:
Cylinder form that is stretched to different modes and rhythms. 
Textures and materials, colors, different view, all of this has 
made the collection express thousands of words with its own language. 
Part of this project is written with the GLSL shading language.
Made in javascript & Webgl(GLSL)
It may take time to load.
Press "s" to download a jpg image (if"opened" in full page)

metadata.name: extrema #210
metadata.description:
speculative topology

16 distinct color palettes, taken mostly from oil paintings

made with clojurescript and webgl

may not render properly on phones or low-end devices

controls:
"b" toggle borders
"s" save image at current screen dimensions
"d" save image at custom dimensions (you will be prompted for the dimensions)

metadata.name: Before the Storm #56
metadata.description:
"Before the Storm" captures a fleeting moment of calmness amidst an impending tempest. Heavy clouds loom overhead, suffusing the air with palpable moisture and an alluring aroma. Majestic evergreens stand tall and proud, bravely facing the ominous yet strangely inviting sky. The air crackles with electrifying energy, foreshadowing the raw power of nature about to be unleashed. In this fleeting moment, one cannot help but be mesmerized by the sublime forces at play, but beware, the calm will not last forever.

Technical Note:
If you wish to render a high-quality version of your iteration, I strongly recommend increasing the resolution (press "R") and setting anti-aliasing to >1 (press "A"). However, be aware that it might take longer to compile and may not render at all on older hardware. To save the image, press "S".

The code has been tested on my old MacBook and on various Windows machines. For best results, use a modern Chromium-based browser, and make sure your browser supports WebGL 2.

superbialux

metadata.name: FERAL #220
metadata.description:
FERAL tries to continue to explore further where PRIMAL left by adding more layers of noise to shape, distort and warp a grid to create topologies...

Enjoy and thanks a million times for being a part of my journey!
